The '''Children's Hospital Association''' ('''CHA'''), is an organization of [[children's hospital]]s with more than 200 members in the [[United States]], [[Australia]], [[Canada]], [[Italy]], [[Mexico]] and [[Puerto Rico]].<ref>https://www.childrenshospitals.org/About-Us/About-the-Association] website</ref>
CHA has offices located in [[Lenexa, Kansas]] and [[Washington, D.C.|Washington, D.C]]. {{Infobox company | name = | logo = | hq_location_city = Washington, D.C., Lenexa, Kansas | hq_location_country = United States | key_people = Mark Wietecha CEO | products = | owner = <!-- or: | owners = --> | num_employees = 150 | num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (if known) --> | parent = | website = https://www.childrenshospitals.org/ }}
