'''''Scarlet Ribbons: A Priest with AIDS''''' is a biography written by [[Rosemary Bailey (author)|Rosemary Bailey]] about the life of her brother, [[Simon Bailey (priest)|Simon Bailey]] who was an Anglican priest and writer.

Simon Bailey became more known to the public after the airing of a [[BBC]] Everyman documentary programme, called ''Simon's Cross''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://genome.ch.bbc.co.uk/e47d80da200f4d7189785f5d8757c244|title=Everyman|work=bbc.co.uk|accessdate=26 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1808892/|title="Everyman" Simon's Cross (TV Episode 1995)|work=IMDb|accessdate=26 May 2015}}</ref> The documentary aired
on 15 January 1995. After the broadcast his sister, Rosemary Bailey wrote an article for [[The Independent]] called ''A Parish Learns to be Positive''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/a-parish-learns-1568069.html|title=A PARISH LEARNS|work=The Independent|accessdate=26 May 2015}}</ref> Subsequently after the documentary and article Rosemary Bailey wrote her brother's biography, ''Scarlet Ribbons: A Priest with AIDS''.<ref>{{cite book | title=Scarlet Ribbons: A Priest with AIDS | publisher=[[Serpent's Tail]]| year=1997 | isbn= 1-85242-521-0}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uic.edu/depts/lib/aidsbkrv/No50.html#909|title=AIDS BOOK REVIEW JOURNAL No. 50|work=uic.edu|accessdate=26 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | title=Scarlet Ribbons: A Priest with AIDS | publisher=Jorvik Press| year=2017 | isbn= 978-0-9863770-3-7}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/aids-gay-reverend-simon-bailey-priest-south-yorkshire-mining-community-support-disease-rosemary-a7861246.html|title=HOW A YORKSHIRE MINING COMMUNITY SUPPORTED THEIR GAY REVEREND WITH AIDS IN THE 1990S|work=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=26 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/family/brother-priest-aids-turned-whole-community-around/|title=My brother was the 'priest with Aids' - here's how he turned a whole community around|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.halifaxcourier.co.uk/news/sister-s-moving-account-of-her-brother-s-battle-with-aids-republished-1-8686326|title=Sister’s moving account of her brother’s battle with Aids republished|work=Halifax Courier|accessdate=4 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/news/health/life-of-gay-sheffield-priest-who-died-from-aids-chronicled-as-moving-book-is-re-published-1-8644754|title=Life of gay Sheffield priest who died from AIDS chronicled as moving book is re-published|work=Sheffield Star|accessdate=12 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/incredible-story-priest-who-died-10853013|title=Incredible story of priest who died of AIDs and the tough pit village who provided him comfort|work=[[Daily Mirror]]|accessdate=22 July 2017}}</ref>

