[[File:Electronic Cigarette Vuse Vapor (25842028390).jpg|thumb|A VUSE electronic cigarette.|alt=A VUSE electronic cigarette.]]
'''Vuse Digital Vapor Cigarette''', commonly known as '''Vuse''' (rhymes with "news"<ref name=Mangan>{{cite news |last1=Mangan |first1=Dan |title=Reynolds American Sees E-Cigarette Launch as a 'Game Changer' |url=https://www.cnbc.com/id/100796458 |accessdate=28 August 2018 |work=CNBC |issue=6 June 2013}}</ref>), is an [[electronic cigarette]] produced by [[R. J. Reynolds Vapor Company]], a subsidiary of [[Big Tobacco]] company [[Reynolds American]]. In 2015, it was the most popular e-cigarette in the United States with 33 percent market share in [[Nielsen ratings|Nielsen]]-tracked channels (a declining proportion of the total).<ref name="cspn_Niel">{{Cite web| title = Nielsen: Electronic Cigarette Sales Growth Declines| author = Melissa Vonder Haar| work = CSPnet| date = 18 August 2015 | accessdate = 13 September 2015| url = http://www.cspnet.com/category-news/tobacco/articles/nielsen-electronic-cigarette-sales-growth-declines}}</ref> Also in 2015, it was the best selling e-cigarette device in convenience stores in the US.<ref name="jour_'Vap">{{Cite web| title = 'Vapers,' vendors say they are here to stay| last = Craver |first=Richard | work = Winston-Salem Journal| date = 4 September 2015| accessdate = 14 September 2015| url = http://www.journalnow.com/news/local/vapers-vendors-say-they-are-here-to-stay/article_7cc260db-b33d-5b44-abaa-2f34a7569b45.html}}</ref> However, Vuse lost its top position in 2017, when [[JUUL]]  overtook it to become the most popular e-cigarette in the US.<ref name=Craver0818>{{cite news |last1=Craver |first1=Richard |title=Juul expands e-cig market share gap with Reynolds' Vuse |url=https://www.journalnow.com/business/juul-expands-e-cig-market-share-gap-with-reynolds-vuse/article_0bb4d442-fc0f-5c00-8b05-29bbf95dc985.html |accessdate=28 August 2018 |work=Winston-Salem Journal |date=25 August 2018}}</ref> {{Asof|2018|08}}, Vuse controls 9.6 percent of the American e-cigarette market, compared to JUUL's 72.1 percent market share, according to Nielsen data.<ref name=Craver0818 />

Vuse has a [[nicotine]] content of 4.8 percent,<ref name=Lynn2013/> which is high compared to other e-cigarettes.<ref name=Lynn2013>{{cite news|url=https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2427721,00.asp|author=Samara Lynn|title=Vuse Digital Vapor Cigarettes|work=[[PC Magazine]]|date=27 November 2013}}</ref>

==History==
R.J. Reynolds launched Vuse in a June 2013 press conference, the first time R.J. Reynolds launched a product with a press conference in two decades.<ref name=Mangan /><ref name=Sebastian>{{cite news |last1=Sebastian |first1=Michael |last2=McDermott |first2=John |title=Is Big Tobacco Back as a Big Advertiser? |url=http://adage.com/article/media/big-tobacco-spending-ads-e-cigarettes/241993/ |accessdate=28 August 2018 |work=Ad Age |date=10 June 2013}}</ref> R.J. Reynolds promoted Vuse with print, [[direct mail]], and [[TV advertising]], the latter of which is highly unusual for [[tobacco products]] in the United States.<ref name=Sebastian /> Vuse was launched in [[Colorado]],<ref name=Sebastian /><ref name="mili_Exch">{{Cite web| title = Exchanges now sell e-cigarettes, but military officials haven’t sorted out all the rules| author = Patricia N Kime| work = MilitaryTimes| date = 25 July 2013| accessdate = 14 September 2015| url = http://www.militarytimes.com/story/military/pt365/2013/07/25/exchanges-now-sell-e-cigarettes-but-military-officials-havent-sorted-out-all-the-rules/32127305/}}</ref> but it quickly become available across the rest of the United States.<ref name=Craver0818 /> In 2015, Jerod Harris filed a lawsuit against Vuse for "[failure] to inform customers of the potential health risks incurred by using the products; specifically, inhalation of the carcinogens formaldehyde and acetaldehyde," a violation of [[California]] state law.<ref name="lawy_Week">{{Cite web| title = Facebook, E-Cigarettes, RV Refrigerators| author = Lucy C| work = LawyersandSettlements.com Legal Blog| date = 11 September 2015| accessdate = 14 September 2015| url = http://www.lawyersandsettlements.com/blog/week-adjourned-9-11-15-facebook-e-cigarettes-rv-refrigerators.html}}</ref>

In April 2018, R.J. Reynolds Vapor Company issued a recall of Vuse Vibe devices.<ref name=Bollinger2018/> It stated that the batteries of Vuse Vibe vaporizers were malfunctioning and overheating after injuries were reported.<ref name=Bollinger2018/> The cause of the malfunction has not been disclosed.<ref name=Bollinger2018>{{cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/triad/news/2018/04/16/reynolds-american-subsidiary-issues-recall-of-e.html|title=Reynolds American subsidiary issues recall of e-cigarette power units|author=Luke Bollinger|publisher=[[The Business Journals]]|date=16 April 2018}}</ref>

In August 2018, Vuse launched the Vuse Alto,<ref>{{cite web |title=vuse alto |url=https://vusevapor.com/advertise/landing-page/key/alto-welcome?SID=Homepage_Hero-AltoIntro |website=RJR Vapors |accessdate=28 August 2018}}</ref> a pod mod-type vaporizer, which is the variant of e-cigarette that JUUL is.<ref name=Craver_rival>{{cite news |last1=Craver |first1=Richard |title=Reynolds Vapor prepares national launch of new e-cig rival to Juul |url=https://www.journalnow.com/business/reynolds-vapor-prepares-national-launch-of-new-e-cig-rival/article_7ba10442-d438-575e-af23-794173089a8a.html |accessdate=28 August 2018 |work=Winston-Salem Journal |date=17 July 2018}}</ref> The Alto is marketed as a direct competitor to JUUL.<ref name=Craver_rival />

